translated: Johansson, Märta Linnea^ Bachelor of Theology, high school teacher, Eksjö, born December 23, 1895 in Rogberga, Jönköping county, daughter of A. and Hanna J. - Graduated from high school in Lund in 1916, graduated with a Bachelor's degree in theology and philosophy in 1917, received a Bachelor of Theology degree in 1920. Substitute teacher in Sollefteå from 1920-1921, in Norrbärke from 1922-1924 and from 1925-1929, temporary teacher in Gävle in 1930-1931, permanent teacher there in 1931. Adjunct professor in Christian and Historical Studies and Social Studies at Eksjö from 1937. Married in 19xx.
